367enum iav_aisp_nn_type {
368 /*
369 * For both 1080p and 4K NN, there is 1 MD model; and 2 C2Y models : 1 C2Y_R model,
370 * 1 C2Y_L model.
371 *
372 * For MD NN :
373 * it is same for 1080p and 4K case, just load it once.
374 *
375 * For C2Y NN :
376 * There are 2 tiles for 1080p case, so just need load 1 C2Y_R and 1 C2Y_L.
377 * However there are 4 tiles for 4K case (3 left tiles and 1 right tile).
378 * To save memory, APP just still load once C2Y_L NN, but prepare 3 run_dag_cmds.
379 * IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_C2Y_L0, IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_C2Y_L1, IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_C2Y_L2
380 * are for different tiles with different run_dag_cmd but from the same C2Y_L NN.
381 */
382 IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_MD = 0,
383 IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_C2Y_R = 1,
384 IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_C2Y_L0 = 2,
385 IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_C2Y_L1 = 3,
386 IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_C2Y_L2 = 4,
387
388 IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_TOTAL_NUM = 8,
389};
390

395 IAV_ISP_NN_MD = 0,
396 IAV_ISP_NN_CE = 1,
397 IAV_ISP_NN_TOTAL_NUM = 2,
398};

407 IAV_ISP_NN_TYPE_MD_TONE_MAPPING = 3,

417};

439 int minor;

444 u32 dsp_version;
445 u32 iav_api_version;
446 u32 iav_api_mode_time;
447};

452};

470struct iav_dsp_vp_cfg {
471 u32 vp_enable : 1;
472 u32 reserved : 31;
473 u32 cmd_addr;
474 u32 cmd_size;
475 u32 msg_addr; // including msg queue info and msg queue
476 u32 msg_size;
477 u32 vp_algo_id;
478};

480struct iav_vp_nn_if_map {
481 u8 dvi_id;
482 u8 start;
483 u8 cnt;
484 u8 reserved0;
485 u8 id[IAV_CUSTOM_NN_IF_MAP_ID_NUM];
486};
487
488struct iav_vp_nn_if_info {
489 struct iav_vp_nn_if_map map[IAV_AISP_MAP_TYPE_NUM];
491};
492
493struct iav_custom_aisp_cfg {
494 u32 fifo_addr;
495 u32 fifo_len;
496 u32 dag_addr;
499 u32 if_num : 4;
500 u32 reserved : 28;
501
502 unsigned long dag_addr_virt_addr; /* Memory address where stores dag_addr. Read only.*/
503 unsigned long port_map_virt_addr; /* Memory address where stores port map of each interface. Read only.*/
504 unsigned long poke_map_virt_addr; /* Memory address where stores poke map of each interface. Read only.*/
505
506 struct iav_vp_nn_if_info if_info[IAV_CUSTOM_NN_IF_NUM];
516};
517
518struct iav_aisp_nn_info {
519 unsigned long dag_addr_phys_addr; /* Memory physical address where stores dag_addr.*/
520 unsigned long port_map_phys_addr; /* Memory physical address where stores port map of each interface.*/
521};
522
523struct iav_isp_nn_info {
524 unsigned long dag_addr_phys_addr; /* Memory physical address where stores dag_addr.*/
525 unsigned long port_map_phys_addr; /* Memory physical address where stores port map of each interface.*/
526 u32 reserved1[4];
527};
528
529/* img_also should prepare all Ambarella AISP cfg info in continous memory, and then feed each
530 * info base physical address to IAV, IAV bypass these addresses to DSP.
531 */
532struct iav_aisp_cfg {
533 u8 active_type_cnt;
534 u8 max_dag_cnt;
535 u8 reserved0[2];
536
537 u32 fifo_addr;
538 u32 fifo_len;
540 struct iav_aisp_nn_info nn_info[IAV_AISP_NN_TYPE_TOTAL_NUM];
543 u32 reserved1[16];
544};
545
546struct iav_isp_nn_cfg {
547 u8 chan_id;
548 u8 reserved0[3];
549 enum iav_isp_nn_type type;
550 u8 active_type_cnt;
551 u8 max_dag_cnt;
552 u8 reserved1[2];
553
554 u32 fifo_addr;
555 u32 fifo_len;
557 struct iav_isp_nn_info nn_info[IAV_ISP_NN_TOTAL_NUM];
560 u32 reserved2[16];
561};
562
563struct iav_aisp_params {
564 enum iav_aisp_type type;
565 union {
566 struct iav_aisp_cfg aisp;
567 struct iav_custom_aisp_cfg custom_aisp;
568 } arg;
569};
570
571struct iav_isp_nn_params {
572 enum iav_isp_nn_cfg_type cfg_type;
573 union {
574 struct iav_isp_nn_cfg nn_cfg;
575 } arg;
576};
